==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lithotypy
<hw>Li*thot"y*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Litho-</ets> + <ets>-typy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The art or
process of making a kind of hard, stereotype plate, by pressing into a
mold, taken from a page of type or other matter, a composition of gum
shellac and sand of a fine quality, together with a little tar and
linseed oil, all in a heated state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithoxyl</ent>⟦br⟧
